Lunarpine underestimated her speed, he was hoping she'd be afraid of 
his reaction and fly away. Her instincts were good, and the wolf was 
now pissed off. He wasn't mad at her, he was mad at himself. he 
spoke, instead of pounced. He let his prey escape, and make a fool of 
him in the process. Lunarpine wasn't in the mood for play, there was 
no more holding back.

"OK Wing you got me, I'll cook tonight, how's Owl dipped in energeon 
sound?" Now he was truly the hunter, and she would soon learn this 
game wasn't lost that easily.
